<H1 ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">Term Suite</FONT></H1>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><B>Term
Suite</B></FONT> <FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">is the Open
Source and UIMA-based application designed and developed within the
European project <A HREF="http://www.ttc-project.eu/index.php">TTC</A>
(</FONT><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><I>Terminology
Extraction, Translation Tools and Comparable Corpora</I></FONT><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><SPAN STYLE="font-style: normal">)</SPAN></FONT><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">.
It aims at automatically generating bilingual terminologies from
comparable corpora. It already provides supports for several
languages as English, French, German, Spanish Chinese and Russian for
example but other languages can easily be integrated: is is
</FONT><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><I>extensible</I></FONT><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">.</FONT></P>
<H2 CLASS="western" ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">Synopsis</FONT></H2>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><B>Term
Suite</B> displays 8 buttons that can be gathered into 3 categories:</FONT></P>
<UL>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">the
	buttons <B>Tagger</B>, <B>Termer</B>, <B>Contextualizer</B> and
	<B>Aligner</B> gathers the core functionalities for generating
	bilingual terminologies from comparable corpora;</FONT></P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">the
	button <B>Converter</B> provides utilities for converting <B>Term
	Suite</B> results into human readable file formats.</FONT></P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">the
	buttons <B>About</B>, <B>Help</B> and <B>Quit</B> makes possible to
	display help messages and to quit.</FONT></P>
</UL>
<H2 CLASS="western"><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">Architecture</FONT></H2>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif"><B>Term
Suite</B> has been designed for generating bilingual terminologies
from comparable corpora according to these 4 step architecture (and
their corresponding tool):</FONT></P>
<OL>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">monolingual
	linguistic analysis (<B>Tagger</B>);</FONT></P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">monolingual
	terminology extraction (<B>Termer</B>);</FONT></P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">monolingual
	terminology contextualization (<B>Contextualizer</B>);</FONT></P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=JUSTIFY><FONT FACE="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">bilingual
	terminology alignment (<B>Aligner</B>).</FONT></P>
</OL>
